      "2025 now covers ASD (monthly 18m/24m + governorate risk), Down Syndrome (governorate registry), Maternal Care (by wilayat), Family Planning / contraceptive (by wilayat), and Newborn Screening - extracted from the three 2025 source workbooks.",
      "Cross-check (confirms accuracy): Birth Spacing 2025 = 2,953 matched the KPI deck exactly; anaemia 28.5% and ANC ~12,433-12,488 matched; Child Maltreatment 2023=92 / 2024=195 and Congenital Anomalies sector splits matched the web app exactly.",
      "Governorate granularity differs by indicator: 2023-2024 had per-health-center detail for some dashboards; 2025 ASD/DS are governorate-aggregate (per-center 2025 not in the source files), while 2025 maternal/contraceptive are available by wilayat.",
      "Maternal Deaths: still no 2025 count in any source file (review meetings referenced only).",
      "Stillbirth detailed monthly & ICD-PM tables are labelled 2024 (final surveillance) in the Nov-2025 deck; the 2025 headline (116 cases, 14 review meetings) is shown separately.",
      "Minor source differences kept in cells: ANC 2024 12,753 (web)/12,754 (deck); ANC 2025 12,433 (deck)/12,488 (sum of centers); anaemia 2024 34.0%/34.4%."
    ]
